                                        String keyColumnName,
                                        String valColumnName,
                                        JdbcConnector jdbcConnector,
                                        Logger log)
        Creates a dictionary of (key,value) pairs of all items read from a table in a DBMS over a JDBC connection.
        Parameters:
        tableName - Name of the table that holds the attribute data.
        keyColumnName - Name of the attribute holding the entity identifiers (keys)
        valColumnName - Name of the attribute containing a given value attribute (e.g., name) of these entities.
        jdbcConnector - The JDBC connection that provides access to the table.
        log - Handle to the log file for keeping messages and statistics.
        Returns:
        A dictionary (i.e., a hash map) of the (key,value) pairs.

      • importFromCsvFile

        public HashMap<K,V> importFromCsvFile(String inputFile,
                                      int maxLines,
                                      int colKey,
                                      int colValue,
                                      String columnDelimiter,
                                      boolean header,
                                      Logger log)
        Creates a dictionary of (key,value) pairs of all items read from a CSV file. ASSUMPTION: Input data collection consists of pairs of identifiers (KEY) and elements (VALUE)
        Parameters:
        inputFile - Path to the input CSV file or its URL at a remote server containing the attribute data.
        maxLines - Number of the first lines to read from the file, skipping the rest; if a negative value is specified, all lines will be consumed.
        colKey - Ordinal number of the attribute holding the entity identifiers.
        colValue - Ordinal number of the column containing a given value attribute (e.g., name) of these entities.
        columnDelimiter - Delimiter character between columns in the file.
        header - Boolean indicating that the first line contains the names of the attributes.
        log - Handle to the log file for keeping messages and statistics.
        Returns:
        A dictionary (i.e., a hash map) of the (key,value) pairs.
